---
// My Approach to Code & Tech
---

<section class="py-20 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 bg-text-secondary/30">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <div class="text-center mb-16">
      <p class="uppercase text-sm tracking-widest text-gray-500 font-medium mb-4">Philosophy</p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold text-black mb-6">
        My Approach to <span class="text-yellow-400">Code</span>
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
        How I think about technology, problem-solving, and building things that matter.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-12">
      
      <!-- Code Philosophy -->
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-black mb-4">Code is Communication</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            I believe code should tell a story. When I write functions, I'm not just solving a problem—I'm leaving breadcrumbs for the next developer (often future me). Clean, readable code isn't just nice to have; it's respect for your teammates and your future self.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            My economics background taught me that efficiency matters, but premature optimization is the enemy. I focus on writing code that works, is easy to understand, and can evolve with changing requirements.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-2xl p-6 border-l-4 border-yellow-400">
          <div class="mb-4">
            <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-yellow-400 mb-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12h6m-6 4h6m2 5H7a2 2 0 01-2-2V5a2 2 0 012-2h5.586a1 1 0 01.707.293l5.414 5.414a1 1 0 01.293.707V19a2 2 0 01-2 2z"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <blockquote class="text-gray-800 italic leading-relaxed">
            "Any fool can write code that a computer can understand. Good programmers write code that humans can understand."
          </blockquote>
          <cite class="text-gray-600 text-sm mt-2 block">— Martin Fowler</cite>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Problem Solving -->
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
        <div class="order-2 md:order-1 bg-gray-50 rounded-2xl p-8">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-black mb-4">My Problem-Solving Process</h4>
          <div class="space-y-3">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <div class="w-6 h-6 bg-yellow-400 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
                <span class="text-xs font-bold text-black">1</span>
              </div>
              <div>
                <p class="font-medium text-gray-800">Understand the Why</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">What problem are we actually solving? Who benefits?</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <div class="w-6 h-6 bg-yellow-400 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
                <span class="text-xs font-bold text-black">2</span>
              </div>
              <div>
                <p class="font-medium text-gray-800">Break It Down</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Complex problems become simple when you slice them thin.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <div class="w-6 h-6 bg-yellow-400 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
                <span class="text-xs font-bold text-black">3</span>
              </div>
              <div>
                <p class="font-medium text-gray-800">Build, Test, Learn</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Ship fast, iterate faster. Feedback beats perfection.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="order-1 md:order-2">
          <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-black mb-4">Business-First Thinking</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            My economics background shapes how I approach technical decisions. I don't just ask "can we build this?" but "should we build this?" Every line of code has an opportunity cost.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            I've seen too many projects fail not because of bad code, but because they solved the wrong problem. I always start with the user's pain point and work backwards to the technical implementation.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Tech Philosophy -->
      <div class="text-center">
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-gray-50 to-yellow-50 rounded-2xl p-8">
          <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-black mb-6">How I See Technology</h3>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 text-left">
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-black mb-3">Tools, Not Religions</h4>
              <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                I'm not married to any framework or language. React, Vue, Svelte—they're all just tools. I pick whatever solves the problem best, not what's trendy on Twitter.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-black mb-3">Boring is Beautiful</h4>
              <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                I love trying new tech, but production isn't a playground. When building something important, I choose boring, proven solutions over shiny new ones.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-black mb-3">Always Learning</h4>
              <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                Tech moves fast, but fundamentals stay constant. I focus on understanding principles over memorizing syntax. Patterns repeat, tools change.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>